scopecontent.p:
The Meier mss., 1927-2009, consists of the papers of Deborah Willen Meier (1931-), an
            education reformer and the founder of the modern small schools movement in the United
            States. Materials in the collection include schoolwork and childhood writings by Meier;
            personal, political, and professional correspondence; drafts and final copies of many of
            Meier’s writings; writings by others on Meier and her projects; notes for speeches;
            documents on the organization of the Central Park East schools, Mission Hill school, the
            Coalition Campus Schools Project, and other educational initiatives; school newsletters
            and mailings to parents; student work and recorded performances; student assessments;
            conference materials; honors and awards; and video and audio recordings of Meier
            interviews and speeches.

